Prudential Financial Inc. Reduces Position in Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. (BVN)

Roana De Caro |
Martes, Julio 18, 2017







Chartwell Investment Partners LLC reduced its position in Stillwater Mining Company (NYSE:SWC) by 93.6% during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). Parametric Portfolio Associates LLC now owns 1,662,460 shares of the mining company's stock worth $20,016,000 after buying an additional 157,522 shares during the period. Vanguard Group Inc. owned approximately 8.96% of Stillwater Mining Company worth $187,583,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. PSquared Asset Management AG bought a new position in shares of Stillwater Mining Company during the first quarter worth about $33,274,000.COPYRIGHT VIOLATION NOTICE: "Somewhat Favorable Media Coverage Very Unlikely to Impact Buenaventura Mining Company (BVN) Stock Price" was originally published by BNB Daily and is owned by of BNB Daily. Finally, OMERS ADMINISTRATION Corp boosted its position in shares of Stillwater Mining Company by 19.2% in the first quarter. State of Alaska Department of Revenue now owns 13,440 shares of the mining company's stock valued at $232,000 after buying an additional 340 shares in the last quarter. Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 410,518 shares of the mining company's stock worth $4,653,000 after buying an additional 3,286 shares during the last quarter. Marshall Wace LLP purchased a new stake in Stillwater Mining Company during the first quarter valued at $19,947,000. Symons Capital Management Inc. now owns 30,194 shares of the mining company's stock valued at $522,000 after buying an additional 810 shares in the last quarter. Norges Bank purchased a new stake in Stillwater Mining Company during the fourth quarter valued at $11,290,000. It also owns an electric power transmission company, a hydroelectric plant, a processing plant and an engineering services consulting company and non-controlling interests in various other mining companies.
Shares of Buenaventura Mining (BVN) opened at 12.08 on Tuesday. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $11.99 and a 200-day moving average price of $12.29. Stillwater Mining Company has a one year low of $9.40 and a one year high of $18.00. If you are accessing this piece on another site, it was stolen and reposted in violation of US and worldwide copyright and trademark law. The legal version of this piece of content can be read at https://www.thestockobserver.com/2017/07/17/vanguard-group-inc-increases-position-in-stillwater-mining-company-swc.html.Separately, Royal Bank Of Canada set a $17.00 target price on shares of Stillwater Mining Company and gave the stock a "hold" rating in a research report on Monday, April 10th.07/14/2014 - Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. had its " rating reiterated by analysts at Morgan Stanley. The stock now has an average rating of "Hold" and a consensus target price of $19.00. (Buenaventura) is a precious metals company.




