Prudential Financial Inc. Reduces Position in Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. (BVN)


					Posted by Chloe McGuire on Jul 16th, 2017 // No Comments




Prudential Financial Inc. cut its position in shares of  Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. (NYSE:BVN) by 27.0% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The institutional investor  owned 16,800 shares of the mining company’s stock after selling 6,200 shares during the period. Prudential Financial Inc.’s holdings in Buenaventura Mining Company were worth $202,000 at the end of the most recent quarter. 
A number of other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also recently made changes to their positions in the stock. Comerica Bank raised its position in shares of  Buenaventura Mining Company by 10.1% in the fourth quarter. Comerica Bank now owns 15,555 shares of the mining company’s stock worth $203,000 after buying an additional 1,421 shares during the last quarter.  Dimensional Fund Advisors LP raised its position in shares of  Buenaventura Mining Company by 0.8% in the fourth quarter. Dimensional Fund Advisors LP now owns 410,518 shares of the mining company’s stock worth $4,653,000 after buying an additional 3,286 shares during the last quarter.  Renaissance Technologies LLC raised its position in shares of  Buenaventura Mining Company by 207.0% in the fourth quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 718,920 shares of the mining company’s stock worth $8,109,000 after buying an additional 484,720 shares during the last quarter.  AQR Capital Management LLC purchased a new position in shares of  Buenaventura Mining Company during the fourth quarter worth $131,000.  Finally, Putnam Investments LLC purchased a new position in shares of  Buenaventura Mining Company during the fourth quarter worth $1,389,000. Institutional investors own  49.32% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. alerts:



Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. (NYSE BVN) opened at 11.97 on Friday. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $11.99 and a 200-day moving average price of $12.29. Buenaventura Mining Company Inc. has a one year low of $9.87 and a one year high of $16.45. The stock’s market cap is $3.02 billion. 





